- M. de Maillet from having
observed an increase of Land
on several parts of the coast
of the Mediterranean conceives
that there must be an uniform
law of diminution of [underline]the Sea[/underline]
in consequence of which
the whole surface must
at length become dry land.
- His opinion is very similar to
that ancient one of [underline]Leucippus[/underline].
And He further supposes that
the whole of the Globe in
early ages was covered with

[page]8|MS-DAVY-00603-000-00008|dnpgs63_006pp|100776391[/page]
water; & that from the slow
